        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 10:09AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 1008 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over San Benito Veterans Memorial Academy, or near San
Benito, moving northwest at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Harlingen, San Benito, Raymondville, La Feria, Elsa, Los Fresnos,
Edcouch, Santa Rosa, South Padre Island, and Lyford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
